I think that using model cards as a framework for do I know what I need, like, if you're

00:18:32.719 --> 00:18:37.280
someone who has read the paper, maybe you've written one yourself, and you're in this build

00:18:37.319 --> 00:18:44.479
versus buy situation, looking for either explicitly this model has a model card that I can

00:18:44.479 --> 00:18:50.680
look at or is equivalent information being shared can really help you make a call about

00:18:50.680 --> 00:18:54.400
whether you trust that model for whatever business use case it is.

