00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:17.400
And they're, you know, they're, I'm going to say, I think a very common mode for data

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:26.439
people to function is in a consultant-type role, like, where you're not the person...

00:28:27.400 --> 00:28:32.839
It's very common for data practitioners not to be building the product itself, but to

00:28:32.839 --> 00:28:36.920
be consultants of, like, how is it going building the product?

00:28:36.920 --> 00:28:38.119
Who is doing well?

00:28:38.119 --> 00:28:39.560
How are our customers doing?

00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:40.839
So, if we...

00:28:40.839 --> 00:28:46.520
Let's just be concrete a little bit, say, of this sort of imaginary example of in an

00:28:46.520 --> 00:28:49.959
HR department, we're going to build, we're going to, you know, like, there's a data

00:28:49.959 --> 00:28:55.479
scientist whose kind of consultant role, their people they are serving is the HR department.

00:28:55.479 --> 00:28:58.040
How can we help the HR department do well?

00:28:58.040 --> 00:29:01.959
What if there are multiple people in that HR department that have, like, conflicting

00:29:01.959 --> 00:29:03.560
ideas about what to do?

00:29:04.680 --> 00:29:12.839
I think that the, like, what do we do in these situations is very related to the kind of

00:29:12.839 --> 00:29:20.760
role we have and how do we, like, how do we manage that particular kind of role?

00:29:20.760 --> 00:29:25.400
So, I think to get an answer to this, we have to have clarity about, am I building

00:29:25.400 --> 00:29:28.439
a data product for my company to sell?

00:29:28.439 --> 00:29:32.839
Am I a consultant to make my company, my organization work well?

00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:35.800
And then how do I move forward from there?

00:29:35.800 --> 00:29:39.640
So, tough question, kind of a big discussion.

00:29:39.640 --> 00:29:42.199
I think something that helps us get to that is to have...

00:29:42.199 --> 00:29:46.839
Be clear-minded about the kind of role that we have as a data practitioner in our organization.

